Package: pacmapr
Title: Pairwise Controlled Manifold Approximation Projection (PaCMAP) for R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yiyang", "Sun", email = "yiyangsun32@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Yingfan", "Wang", role = "aut",
           comment = "Author of the original Python PaCMAP implementation"),
    person("PaCMAP contributors", role = "cph")
    )
Description: A native R (and C++) implementation of Pairwise Controlled
    Manifold Approximation Projection (PaCMAP), a dimensionality reduction
    method that preserves both local and global structure by simultaneously
    optimizing over three types of pairs: nearest neighbours, mid-near pairs,
    and further pairs. This package is a re-implementation of the reference
    Python package by Wang et al.; no Python installation is required.
    See Wang, Huang, Rudin & Shaposhnik (2021) <https://www.jmlr.org/papers/v22/20-1061.html>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
